   &UR; INDUSTRIAL JAPAN'S `FORGOTTEN HOLOCAUST' &LR;  &QL;
</P>
<P>
   &UR; JAPBIZ-WARCRIMES-ECONOMIST-575&AMP;add &LR;  &QL;
</P>
<P>
   TOKYO _ ``The shame of our history is now going abroad,'' says
Tadashi Kosho, who has spent his life studying the use of slave
labor by Japanese companies during the Second World War. Enter
Edward Fagan, a New York lawyer and world-class embarrasser. The
man who shamed Swiss bankers and German industrialists into
stumping up billions of dollars for their wartime offenses now
plans to take on the might of Japanese industry. &QL;
</P>
