<TEXT>
<P>
   &QL;  PA Contract Awards By Jimmy Chuang States News Service
Washington, July 7 -- United Defense of York won a $3 million
contract from the U.S. Army Tank-Automotive and Armaments Command
in Warren, Mich., for ground effect vehicles, motor vehicles,
trailers and cycles.
</P>
<P>
   American Hospital Services Group Inc. of Exton won a $2.3
million contract from the Department of Veterans Affairs in Altoona
for medical services.
</P>
<P>
   News Printing Co. Inc. of Claysburg won a $70,402 contract from
the Government Printing Office in Washington for photographic,
mapping, printing and publication services.
</P>
<P>
   Bulova Technologies LLC of Lancaster won a $982,418 contract
from the U.S. Army Operatioins Support Command in Rock Island,
Ill., for ammunition and explosives.
</P>
<P>
   Chant Engineering Co. Inc. of New Britain won a $188,450
contract from the U.S. Navy in Indian Head, Md., for instruments
and laboratory equipment.
</P>
<P>
   Carnegie Mellon University of Pittsburgh won a $50,000 contract
from the U.S. Army Tank-Automotive and Armaments Command in Warren,
Mich., for research and development.
</P>
<P>
   K Technology Corp. of Fort Washington won a $79,838 contract
from the NASA Langley Research Center in Hampton, Va., for special
studies and analyses.
</P>
<P>
   Language Services Associates of Willow Grove won a $8 million
contract from the General Services Administration in Auburn, Wash.,
for professional, administrative and management support services.
</P>
<P>
   -30-
</P>
