rebuilt from the ground up when it turned out that Russian
construction workers had riddled the structure with bugs, officials
say the now-complete building is ``clean'' _ but they still call
the Orthodox Church across the street ``Our Lady of the Immaculate
Reception.'' By Brian Whitmore. 770 words.
