<P>
   &QL;  WASHINGTON WATCH VOTE CHART Questions regarding this
transmission should be directed to 202-628-3100, Ext. 218.
WASHINGTON, July 7 -- The following chart shows how senators and
representatives voted on key bills and amendments within the last
week. A ``Y'' means the member voted for the measure; an ``N''
means the member voted against the measure; a ``?'' means the
member did not vote; and a ``P'' means the member voted
``present.''
</P>
<P>
   THERE ARE NO SENATE VOTES THIS WEEK.
</P>
<P>
   HOUSE VOTES:
</P>
<P>
   1) BILL NUMBER: Collective
</P>
<P>
   The House on June 30 approved, 276-136, a bill to grant doctors
the right to collectively bargain with health plans. Supporters
said it would equalize negotiations between providers and insurers.
Opponents said it would create doctor ``cartels'' that would raise
health care costs. A ``yes'' vote supports the bill.
</P>
<P>
   2) BILL NUMBER: Abortion
</P>
<P>
   The House on June 30 approved, 213-202, an amendment to the
doctors' collective bargaining bill to exempt abortion coverage.
Supporters said the measure would prevent doctors from compelling
health plans to cover abortions. Opponents said it was a ``poison
pill'' intended to stop the legislation. A ``yes'' vote supports
the amendment.
</P>
