<P>
   POTTER _ WEST PALM BEACH, Fla. _ Kids flock to book stores at
12:01 a.m. and snap up hundreds of copies of the new Harry Potter
book.We wrap up the Potter frenzy. (Hayes, Palm Beach Post) WITH
PHOTOS. Moving late.
</P>
<P>
   POTTER-BRAILLE _ ``Harry Potter and the Goblet of Fire'' will be
released in the U.S. on July 8, and the same day Scholastic Press
publishers will transfer the book electronically to the National
Braille Press in Boston _ giving blind readers an unprecedented
early handle the books. To kids like 7-year-old John Herrera of
Atlanta, a fan of the books who is blind, the fast-tracking is
unusual and satisfying. ``It makes a big difference that he'll be
able to get the book near the same time as his friends,'' said
Herrera's mom, Robbyn. ``He won't feel left out.'' (Kicklighter,
Atlanta Journal-Constitution). 10. WITH PHOTOS
</P>
<P>
   STEVEHARVEY-QA _ ``20 Questions For'' actor/comedian Steve
Harvey, who joins legendary R&AMP;B trio the O'Jays for an unusual
line-up of music and laughs Saturday at the Fox Theatre. (SoMurray,
Atlanta Journal-Constitution). 30.
</P>
<P>
   SPORTS
</P>
<P>
   TENNIS
</P>
<P>
   WIMMEN _ Sampras and Agassi play in semifinal matches. (Clarke,
Palm Beach Post)
</P>
<P>
   WITH
</P>
