<P>
   QUAYLE-OBIT (Undated) {ndash} Jim Quayle, father of former
vice-president Dan Quayle, has died. By CHARLES KELLY. Story will
move in the ``A'' category.
</P>
<P>
   HUNT (Phoenix) - The controversy started, best anyone can tell,
May 27, 1999, when several Hopis arrived in the offices of Wupatki
National Monument outside Flagstaff. The members of a clan from
Third Mesa were on a simple errand. For religious purposes -
approved by government permit, no less - could they take a golden
eaglet from their ancestral grounds on the monument? Yes, it would
be killed and its feathers used as part of a ceremony. The request
was denied, and what started out as a simple errand has now become
the hinge upon which a national policy turns. The Hopis want a
golden eaglet. The National Park Service wants to obey the law and
its own rules. And a contentious issue with wide-ranging precedents
is about to split open. By JUDD SLIVKA. Story will move in the
``A'' category.
</P>
<P>
   BORDERAIR (Undated) - The U.S. Border Patrol is borrowing
airplanes from across the country to fly extra missions of mercy
along Arizona's remote frontier as the death toll rises among
illegal border crossers.
</P>
<P>
   The Tucson sector, which includes most of Arizona's border with
Mexico, has been this year's hotspot in the nation for immigrants
in distress, the Border Patrol said. The numbers tell the story:
844 people rescued and 52 dead since October.
</P>
<P>
   The sector's rescues accounted for roughly 60 percent of all
immigrant rescues along the nation's southwest border. The number
of deaths is already nearly twice that of last year's. By PAT
FLANNERY. Story will move in the ``A'' category.
</P>
