   DNC-BUSINESSES (Los Angeles) _ Despite a closed-door meeting
with police and city officials who mapped out their strategy for
containing protests, downtown Los Angeles business owners said they
are no more confident their property and lives will be protected
during the Democratic National Convention. By Erik Nelson. (Will
move in the ``a'' national and ``n'' California news files.)
