   BC-RACE-PLANTATION-NYT (moved on Wednesday, June 21) &QL;
</P>
<P>
   A New York Times News Service article sent on Wednesday, June
21, about the historical and racial implications of a plan for a
national park on Magnolia Plantation in Louisiana misstated the
educational record of Viola Cowles, the mother of the park's
historical interpreter. Mrs. Cowles graduated from high school and
took some college courses. The article also misspelled the names of
the park's superintendent, Laura Soulliere, and a member of the
plantation's founding family, Mary Catallo. It also misstated Ms.
Catallo's occupation. She is an executive of an engineering firm.  &QL;
</P>
