with their friends. Her audience consists of a million and a half
people -- mostly women over 30. Her audience, nearly twice the size
of those for competing talk shows, earns the station nearly $1
million a year in revenue, a remarkable figure for a daytime show.
Hamburg in a studio at WOR where she has been broadcasting for 21
years. (Sara Krulwich/The New York Times)
