FAKE-HANDBAGS -- There is a new breed of sidewalk shopper that have
style and can afford to pay retail prices but enjoy the thrill of
adding a $30 counterfeit item to their wardrobes. Where the
shoppers likely to inspect merchandise by street vendors were once
mainly office workers and tourists, now they are as likely to be
chic passers-by, clutching a genuine Prada shoulder bag or a tote
emblazoned with the real Gucci logo. Lauren Strax, a college
student from Houston, Texas, checking out handbags on 60th Street
in Manhattan. (Nancy Siesel/The New York Times) LITE
</P>
