<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-BBO-ANGELS-NOTES-LADN </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
OTHER TEAMS EYE BOTTENFIELD
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By JOE HAAKENSON  
 San Gabriel Valley Tribune  
<TEXT>
<P>
   ANAHEIM -- Pitcher Kent Bottenfield is drawing attention from
teams around the league looking for pitching help, and there
figures to be more scouts than normal at Edison Field Sunday for
his start against the Rockies.
</P>
<P>
   The Angels aren't necessarily shopping Bottenfield, but he is in
his free-agent season and so far the Angels haven't made any
attempts to re-sign him beyond this season.
</P>
<P>
   ``There's nothing going on,'' Bottenfield said of talks with the
Angels. ``I haven't heard anything about their interest in doing
anything. I would assume I'll be a (trade) candidate in the next
few weeks. Being a free agent it's only natural.''
</P>
<P>
   Bottenfield was acquired along with second baseman Adam Kennedy
in a trade with the Cardinals for Jim Edmonds on March 23. He is
making $4 million this season and said he'd like to talk to the
Angels about returning next season.
</P>
<P>
   ``We let them know at one point a while back we were interested
in listening,'' Bottenfield said. ``I have high respect for
(manager) Mike (Scioscia) and (pitching coach) Buddy (Black). I
like the players here, I like the situation here. That's where it
was left.''
</P>
<P>
   Bottenfield said his agent contacted the Angels sometime in late
April. But Angels general manager Bill Stoneman said he will not
discuss the contract status of any players.
</P>
<P>
   ``That's something best left between employer and employee,''
Stoneman said. ``Usually it works better if you don't make it a
public issue.''
</P>
<P>
   Bottenfield, 31, won 18 games last season and was named to the
National League All-Star team. This season he's struggled, going
4-7 with a 5.78 ERA. He also spent time on the disabled list with
tendinitis in his right shoulder.
</P>
<P>
   Pitcher Tim Belcher was suspended and fined and undisclosed
amount for his actions during the game against the Mariners June 27
in Seattle. Belcher disputed a balk call and lost his temper after
being ejected from the game. The Major League office said the
suspension was a result of Belcher arguing excessively and causing
physical contact with an umpire, in this case homeplate umpire Mike
DiMuro.
</P>
<P>
   Belcher is currently on the disabled list with a strained muscle
in his right elbow and cannot begin serving the suspension until he
returns.
</P>
<P>
   Which pitcher on the Angels staff has the best ERA? Would you
believe Mike Fyhrie, at 2.45?
</P>
<P>
   Fyhrie's role is as a long man, which has become important
recently with the abbreviated starts of Belcher and Ken Hill. He
has pitched as long as 4 fr 2/3 innings and been able to keep the
team in the game after falling behind by large margins early.
</P>
<P>
   Formerly a starter, Fyhrie said the transition to long man has
gone smoothly.
</P>
<P>
   ``Last year I went from starter to reliever, so there was a
transition period,'' he said. ``This year I'm more comfortable with
it. When I came into spring training they told me I was going to be
a reliever. So I could focus on that, getting ready quickly and
going right after hitters.''
</P>
<P>
   Pitcher Scott Schoeneweis (strained rib-cage muscle) came out of
his Thursday bullpen workout fine on Friday and will throw a
simulated game Sunday. If all goes well, Schoeneweis will begin a
rehab assignment soon and could be back in the rotation in two to
three weeks.
</P>
<P>
   DAILY BOX
</P>
<P>
   ANGELS VS. COLORADO
</P>
<P>
   Time: 1:05 at Edison Field
</P>
<P>
   TV/Radio: FOX Channel 11; KLAC-570, XPRS-1090
</P>
<P>
   Matchup: Ken Hill (4-5, 7.35 ERA) will start for Anaheim against
Colorado's Brian Bohanon (4-5, 6.20). Hill felt tightness in his
upper back in his last start, getting knocked around for five runs
in 1 fr 2/3 innings against the Mariners. If Hill does not bounce
back strong today, his days in the rotation could be numbered.
</P>
<P>
   -- Joe Haakenson
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
